    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-12T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="682"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5741: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-13T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 13, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 13—5:14
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Department’s 46, February 11, 1 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d682fn88">Not
                        printed.</note> In the light of comments made in my 116, February 4, 11
                    a.m., I recommend that we take no action on this loan other than possibly to ask
                    for a copy of the agreement in view of its possible bearing upon status of Boxer
                    Indemnity payments.<note n="89" xml:id="d682fn89">For correspondence concerning
                        Boxer Indemnity payments, see <ref target="#pg_660">pp. 660</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
